Q1  Write a Python program that prompts the user to enter their name and then prints a greeting message in the format "Hello, {Your Name}!".
Solution: 
name = input("Enter your name: ")
print(f"Hello, {name}!")
Q2 Write a Python program that takes a sentence as input and prints the reverse of each word in the sentence. For example, if the input is "Hello World!", the output should be "olleH dlroW!".
Solution: 
String = input("Enter a sentence: ")
words = String.split()
for word in words:
    print(word[::-1], end=" ")
